Class PAMLParameterSet

      edu.umaryland.igs.idea.PAMLParameterSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
public class PAMLParameterSet
extends ParameterSet

PAMLParameterSet represents a grouping of PAML parameters. There is only one PAMLParameterSet in an IDEAConfiguration, and it contains only those parameters read from and written to PAML's .ctl file. If the user wishes to save values for IDEA-specific parameters, the alternate .idea format (which also incorporates the PAML parameters) must be used. PAMLParameterSet overrides ParameterSet to provide methods for parsing and writing .ctl files.

Parameters:

Throws:
FileNotFoundException - if the file is not found or a gunzip-related error occurs

Method Detail

save

void save(String codemlFilename)
    throws FileNotFoundException
The save method writes the PAMLParameterSet to the specified file. The file is written in .ctl format. This method makes use of the one-arg toString method in Parameter.

Parameters:
codemlFilename - the name of the .ctl file to write
Throws:
FileNotFoundException - if the file is a directory, cannot be created or cannot be opened

getComment

public static String getComment(String line)
The static method getComment returns the part of a .ctl-file line that is a comment (not including the *). If the line contains no comment or a comment with only spaces, it returns null.

Parameters:
line - the string from which to extract the comment
Returns:
a String representing the part of the line that is a comment
